comment.content:
It is stored in HttpContext(or CallContext in non web environments) and retrieved from there every time a NhOuterTransactionScope is created. However the pulling from httpContext is encapsulated by a SessionManager class and a UnitOfWork framework that all works alongside of StructureMap. The result is that creating a TransactionScope is as simple as:

using (var scope = sessionManager.CreateTransactionScope())
{
    ...
}
